1. Create a folder for your git repository and initialize the new git repository in that folder.

	mkdir git1
	cd git1/
	git init
Result:Initialized empty Git repository in /home/mery/git1/.git/
	 git config --local user.name "MaryFljyan"
	 git config --local user.email "mary.fljyan.g@tumo.org"
	 git config --local  core.editor vim

2. Create a branch with your name and write a program in any programming language to print some message.

	git checkout -b mery
	vim file.txt
	#!/bin/bash


	echo Hello word from Mery !


3. Add remote to your local repository.


	git remote add origin https://github.com/MaryFljyan/Git-ITC.git


4. Commit and push your branch to remote repository.
    
	git status
	git add file.txt
	git commit
	git push -u origin mery

5. Create a tag for the last commit in your branch and push that tag to remote repository.
	git log
	git tag tag1 48bc67772ecf9df9b030f8f8a0f7ca8b046a178b 
	git tag
	git push --tags

6. Create pull request for your branch.

	git push -u origin master
	click pull request
	base:masteer -> compare:mery
	add message
	click create pull request
    	click merged

7.Create a pre-commit hook to show some messages.
	cd ./.git
	cd /hooks
	mv pre-commit.sample pre-commit
	vim pre commit
	delete all programs
	write echo "Hello world from Mery!"
	bash pre-all commit
